ablaze having fallen on its side directly in front of a petrol station. “The agency’s officials and men of the Lagos State Fire Service and the Federal Fire Service battled to save the situation from causing extensive damage. “The tanker, while negotiating a bend in front of Nigeria National Petroleum Corporation NNPC, fuel station lost control and fell on its side and caught fire. “One dead, and about 15 people got injured. The fuel station was, however, not affected “The raging fire was later curtailed and extinguished and surrounding buildings protected from being gutted.” Vanguard AT the popular Mobil Petrol Station on Oba Akran Avenue, Ikeja, Lagos, five vehicles that were on a queue and another truck that brought in fresh supply of fuel were, yesterday, consumed in a fire incident in which one person was critically injured. March 20, 2014 In "News" What could have been a major tragedy was on Saturday averted by the combined efforts of the Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) and the Lagos State Fire Service when a tanker fully loaded with 33,000 litres of PMS fell on the Anthony Bridge Inward Gbagada. December 24, 2016 In "News" By Olasunkanmi Akoni Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, (LASEMA) early Wednesday morning, averted yet another disaster when it recovered an oil tanker laden with 44,000 litres of Aviation fuel (Jet A1) which involved in a lone accident on the Otedola Bridge inward Berger, along Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. In the operation, LASEMA… November 20, 2019 In "News"